    </name>
    <questiontext format="markdown">
      <text><![CDATA[**32.5 E1 Wave Equation, Single Time Step**

Suppose that \\\( u = u(x, t) \\\) satisfies the wave equation \\\( u_{tt} = c^2 u_{xx} \\\) in \\\( t > 0 \\\) and \\\( 0 < x < {@L@} \\\).

It is given that \\\( u \\\) satisfies the boundary conditions \\\( u(0, t) = u({@L@}, t) = 0 \\\) (\\\( t > 0 \\\)) and initial conditions that need not be stated for the purposes of this question. The application is such that the wave speed \\\( c = 1.4 \\\).

The numerical method

\\\[
u_j^{n+1} = 2u_j^n - u_j^{n-1} + \mu^2(u_{j+1}^n - 2u_j^n + u_{j-1}^n)
\\\]

where \\\( \mu = \frac{c \, \delta t}{\delta x} \\\), is implemented using \\\( \delta x = {@dx@} \\\) and \\\( \delta t = {@dt@} \\\).

Suppose that, after 7 time-steps, the following data forms part of the numerical solution:

{@apply(table,append([[u_j^6,u_j^7]],args(transpose(matrix(u6,u7)))))@}

Carry out the next time-step to find an approximation to \\\( u \\\) at \\\( t = 8 \delta t \\\).


\\\(\mu=\\\) [[input:S_mu]] [[validation:S_mu]] [[feedback:mu]]

\\\(u_j^8\\\) at \\\(t=8\delta t\\\) with at least 4 d.p.
[[input:S_u8]] [[validation:S_u8]] [[feedback:u8]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
